Package org.opengis.filter

Class InvalidFilterValueException

Object
Throwable
Exception
RuntimeException
IllegalArgumentException
InvalidFilterValueException
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
@UML(identifier="InvalidParameterValue", specification=ISO_19143) public class InvalidFilterValueException extends IllegalArgumentException
Thrown if a filter or an expression can not be evaluated for a given parameter. It may be because an expression contains a reference to a value which is not defined in an instance being evaluated.
Since:
3.1
See Also:
Filter.test(Object), Expression.apply(Object), Serialized Form
